Sun.interpretation: The Sun represents soul, vitality, authority, and father. With weak Vimsopaka Bala, Sun's significations may not manifest favorably. The native may face challenges in matters related to Sun and may need remedial measures.

Moon.interpretation: The Moon represents mind, emotions, mother, and public life. With good Vimsopaka Bala, Moon's significations will manifest positively in most areas of life. The native will generally experience favorable outcomes in matters related to Moon.

Mars.interpretation: Mars represents courage, siblings, energy, and competitive spirit. With moderate Vimsopaka Bala, Mars's significations will manifest with mixed results. The native will experience both successes and challenges in matters related to Mars.

Mercury.interpretation: Mercury represents intelligence, communication, education, and analytical abilities. With good Vimsopaka Bala, Mercury's significations will manifest positively in most areas of life. The native will generally experience favorable outcomes in matters related to Mercury.

Jupiter.interpretation: Jupiter represents wisdom, knowledge, children, and fortune. With good Vimsopaka Bala, Jupiter's significations will manifest positively in most areas of life. The native will generally experience favorable outcomes in matters related to Jupiter.

Venus.interpretation: Venus represents love, relationships, comforts, and artistic abilities. With moderate Vimsopaka Bala, Venus's significations will manifest with mixed results. The native will experience both successes and challenges in matters related to Venus.

Saturn.interpretation: Saturn represents discipline, longevity, hardships, and career. With very weak Vimsopaka Bala, Saturn's significations will likely manifest negatively. The native will face significant challenges in matters related to Saturn and should consider appropriate remedial measures.

Rahu.interpretation: Rahu represents obsession, foreign influences, and unconventional pursuits. With good Vimsopaka Bala, Rahu's significations will manifest positively in most areas of life. The native will generally experience favorable outcomes in matters related to Rahu.

Ketu.interpretation: Ketu represents spirituality, detachment, and hidden talents. With very weak Vimsopaka Bala, Ketu's significations will likely manifest negatively. The native will face significant challenges in matters related to Ketu and should consider appropriate remedial measures.
